# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   Documented at https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv#local-version-file
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if platform is not identical, it may cause dependency resolution issues.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Poetry uses poetry.lock to ensure reproducible builds.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   PDM stores project-wide configurations in .pdm.toml
.pdm.toml
.pdm-plugins/

# pipxml
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is co-committed.
#pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/davidhalter/jedi
